[[File:Drechsler Kleines Blumenstilleben.jpg|thumb|right|200px|''Small flower piece'', 1805, now in the [[<U+00D6>sterreichische Galerie Belvedere]]]]
'''Johann Baptist Drechsler''', a [[Still life|painter of flowers]], was born at Vienna in 1766, and became a professor at the [[Academy of Fine Arts Vienna|Academy of that city]]. He died at Vienna in 1811. He painted fruit and flower pieces in imitation of [[Jan van Huysum|Van Huysum]]. There are examples of his work in the [[Hermitage Museum|Hermitage]] at St. Petersburg, and in the [[Kunsthistorisches Museum|Vienna Gallery]].

